The <strong><code>SVGTextPositioningElement</code></strong> interface is implemented by elements that support attributes that position individual text glyphs. It is inherited by <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/SVGTextElement" title="The SVGTextElement interface corresponds to the &lt;text&gt; elements."><code>SVGTextElement</code></a>, <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/SVGTSpanElement" title="The SVGTSpanElement interface represents a &lt;tspan&gt; element."><code>SVGTSpanElement</code></a>, <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/SVGTRefElement" title="The SVGTRefElement interface corresponds to the &lt;tref&gt; elements."><code>SVGTRefElement</code></a> and <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/SVGAltGlyphElement" title="The SVGAltGlyphElement interface represents an &lt;altglyph&gt; element. This interface makes it possible to implement more sophisticated and particular glyph characters. For some textal representations as: ligatures (e.g. æ, ß, etc ), special-purpose fonts (e.g. musical symbols) or even alternate glyphs such as Asian text strings it is required that a different set of glyphs be used than the normal given character data."><code>SVGAltGlyphElement</code></a>.